t color for all 3 types of LearnDash alerts<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>New:<\\/strong> Alerts: Remove alert icons<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>New:<\\/strong> Alerts: Set a border width for all alerts<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Fix:<\\/strong> Quiz buttons now properly inherit your button styles<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Fix:<\\/strong>\\u00a0Alert icon position on smaller screens<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>2.1 - Released Jun 26, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Ribbon colors are back!<\\/strong> Thank you for the feedback. Keep it coming.<\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong>\\u00a0Course Grid: Ribbon background &amp; text colors for default, enrolled, free &amp; custom ribbons<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Fix:<\\/strong> When disabling expand\\/collapse on course content lists, it was also being disabled on the Profile<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>2.0.1 - Released Jun 24, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<p>I\'ve heard your feedback and will be adding back the ability to customize course grid ribbon colors in the next release (~5-8 days).<\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Fix:<\\/strong> Legacy: Button styles were not being properly applied when using the \\\"Legacy\\\" template<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Fix:<\\/strong> Add space for \\\"Download Certificate\\\" button icon, and other small tweaks to buttons within alerts<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Alerts: Vertically center all icons<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Focus Mode: Small improvements to spacing of username in header<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Improved styles when \\\"Mark Complete\\\" button is disabled<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Tweak:<\\/strong> More specific button style to avoid some theme conflicts with link colors<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>2.0 - Released Jun 22, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>IMPORTANT:<\\/strong>\\u00a0LearnDash\'s color settings must be disabled for our plugin\'s colors to take effect<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Now compatible with the LearnDash 3.0 Active Template<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> New style options for focus mode, tooltips, course content, profile &amp; more<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Tons of updated styles for quizzes (no customization; just improved styles)<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Changed:<\\/strong> Options are now saved globally. Styles remain in place even when you switch themes.<\\/li>\\n<li>Official videos &amp; explanations of all settings will be released soon<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>1.7.3 - Released Mar 23, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Changed:<\\/strong> Course Grid: Buttons are now displayed at the very bottom of each grid item<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>1.7.2 - Released Mar 11, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Fixed:<\\/strong>\\u00a0Added a min-width of 45px to the number column in the course content table. This accounts for up to 999 items on most devices &amp; themes, without forcing the number to a new line.<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Fixed:<\\/strong> Course Grid: Inline &amp; full-width buttons both work again<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>1.7.1 - Released Feb 8, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Fixed:<\\/strong> Bug that was preventing administrators from accessing a user\'s \\\"Edit Profile\\\" page in the admin area<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>1.7 - Released Jan 23, 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Set a custom URL for\\u00a0the \\\"Edit Profile\\\" link when using the [ld_profile] shortcode<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Added:<\\/strong> Hide \\\"Enrolled Course Points\\\" in the [ld_profile] shortcode<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Changed:<\\/strong> Small spacing adjustment to the list count numbers in course content tables<\\/li>\\n<li><strong>Changed:<\\/strong> Adjusted alignment of quiz headings when quizzes are displayed in the [ld_profile]\\u00a0shortcode<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><strong>1.6.3 - Released Dec 13, 2018<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Compatibility:<\\/strong> Boss. Theme: We are now compatible with t